I should elaborate on the issue of haafus. Japan is pretty much a homogeneous nation (98% ethnic Japanese). Living as a minority among such a non-diverse group can be pretty hard, especially so in a place like Japan where standoing out is culturally looked down upon to the point that until fairly recently students were forced to have their hair dyed black because a lot of Japanese didn't believe Japanese people don't have hair of any other color. If she was a haafu racially, she might have suffered bullying because of it, because to the Japanese, she'd always look like a foreigner. If she had been an actual immigrant, it might have been worse since they will never see you as Japanese, especially when it comes to being cruel to "the other".
The reason she broke character so easily over trivial latino banter like being called "mestizo" is probably because of this.
I'm making assumptions here since I don't know if she lived in Japan, which part, for how long and which time period.
